Ad Text:
Are you a Solution Architect with strong experience in the Digital domain, looking to secure an almost 2 year contract, running through until December 2027?! If so, keep reading.

A large Federal Government agency are embarking on a once in a lifetime transformation program which will span across 6 years and they are looking for a Digital Solution Architect to join their Solution Architecture practice on a long term contract, which means you get the bonus of contract rates, with strong stability.

The Solution Architecture practice work across a number of large tech projects and programs including their flagship transformation program and they are looking for a strong Solution Architect who has delivered digital initiatives, amongst other technical initiatives to join their team.

They are based in Sydney CBD and currently have a 50% hybrid working policy and a strong culture, with low staff turnover.

Skills and experience required:

Strong solutions architecture experience across a range of projects and programs
TOGAF or ArchiMate Certified
Solid experience working on digital initiatives
Experience architecting solutions in multi-cloud environments
API and integration experience
Driven, proactive and able to work independently
Excellent stakeholder management skills
Experience across various technologies including, but not limited to Boomi, Dynamics 365, OutSystems, .NET, SharePoint, DataBricks, Azure & AWS integrations into a secured environment

Platform Manager – AI & Data Platforms | Melbourne, VIC | Hybrid (3 days onsite)

A major Australian organisation undergoing significant digital and AI transformation is seeking an experienced Platform Manager – AI & Data to lead the next stage of its enterprise platform modernisation. With a national footprint and a mandate to become an AI-enabled business, the organisation is investing heavily in modern AI/ML platform capability, scalable cloud foundations, and contemporary engineering practices.

About the Team
This role sits within a central Data, AI, and Platform Enablement function responsible for building the foundations that power intelligent decision-making, automation, and emerging AI use cases across the organisation.

The team brings together platform engineers, ML engineers, product specialists, and architects to design and operate secure, scalable, cloud-first platforms that support enterprise digital experiences and future AI growth.

About the Role
You’ll lead the strategy, design, build and uplift of the organisation’s AI and data platform ecosystem, working closely with technology, data science, and architecture leadership.

This role is ideal for someone who has previously built or scaled an AI/ML platform, including ingestion, feature engineering, model deployment, observability, and MLOps, and can provide strong people and technical leadership through complex transformation.
  
Key Responsibilities

Own the end-to-end evolution of the organisation’s AI/ML platform, including architecture, engineering standards, and operational excellence.
Champion modern platform engineering: cloud-native patterns, containerisation, microservices, IaC, automation, and MLOps.
Partner with data science and ML teams to enable model training, deployment, monitoring, and lifecycle management.
Work with architecture, security, governance and compliance teams to maintain enterprise standards across AI and data workloads.
Lead cross-functional teams, managing roadmaps, risks, dependencies, and delivery outcomes for complex, multi-stream programs.
Drive platform optimisation across cost, performance, reliability, and scalability.
Foster a culture of experimentation, innovation and engineering excellence, mentoring engineers and uplifting capability across the organisation.
  
About You
You’re a platform and transformation leader who has built or significantly uplifted an AI/ML or data platform at scale, with a strong technical foundation and the ability to guide teams through ambiguity.
We’re Looking For

Experience owning or leading AI/ML platform architecture, build, or modernisation in a large organisation.
Strong background in cloud platforms (Azure preferred; Snowflake, Databricks, Fabric or comparable).
Hands-on knowledge of MLOps, feature stores, model serving, pipelines, orchestration, observability, and ML governance.
Experience leading platform or ML engineering teams in Agile delivery environments.
Familiarity with containers (Docker, Kubernetes), IaC (Terraform, Bicep), and enterprise automation patterns.
Strong stakeholder management, with the ability to influence senior technical and business leaders.
Understanding of enterprise data governance, security, and responsible AI principles.  
Why You’ll Love Working Here

Flexible hybrid working options.
Modern office environment with onsite facilities and employee programs.
Generous employee benefits, discounts, and wellbeing initiatives.
Strong investment in continuous learning, leadership development, and career pathways.
Supportive policies including paid parental leave and long-term incentive programs.  
This position requires candidates to hold Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency. Candidates must also be based in or willing to relocate to Melbourne for the role.

Are you an experienced Software Integration Engineer interested in working with a growing small business and where you can make a real difference?

Location: FLEXIBLE

Please note: only applications complete with a cover letter addressing the below 'Employer questions' will be considered.

Earth Science Information Systems (EScIS) is a trusted global leader in environmental data management software.

Due to business growth we are looking for a Software Integration Engineer to streamline our internal operations, and to contribute to our SaaS application.

Work for a company who values and rewards achievement

Become a vital member of our expanding business

Work from home opportunity

Quarterly team meetings in the Byron Bay/Ballina Region

OUR COMPANY

EarthScience Information Systems (EScIS) produces leading edge software for environmental and hydrogeological data. Our solutions are used by consulting, mining, government, industrial, energy and other firms globally.

OUR PRODUCT

ESdat is an all-in-one environmental data management software. It's a powerful asset for organisations whose success relies on the quality, integrity, and easy accessibility of their data. ESdat has a large and growing worldwide uptake and is available as SaaS and Enterprise deployments.

YOUR ROLE

We are seeking an experienced Software Integration Engineer to design, develop, implement, and maintain integration solutions across our business. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in software engineering, API development, middleware, and system interoperability, with proven experience integrating diverse platforms and applications in enterprise environments.

This role requires a proactive problem-solver with excellent coding, debugging, and communication skills, capable of working both independently and collaboratively in technical environment.

This position is full-time.

Location is work from home or hotdesking with other staff located nearby. If you are in Sydney, we'd like you to come into the office 1-2 days per week.

To be considered for this role, you will have:

Degree in IT, Computer Science, Software Engineering or related discipline

3+ years of experience in Software Integration Engineering.

Experience in working in cloud platforms (preferably Azure) and an understanding of databases

An understanding of the Test and Delivery Process

Proficiency in programming

Familiarity with or an interest in AI and MCP servers will be highly regarded.

Able to work independently and as part of a team

You will be rewarded with …

Full training and support

Competitive remuneration

Work from home or hot desk with nearby staff – if you are in Sydney, we'd like you to come into the office 1-2 days per week

Travel to the Byron Bay/Ballina region one week per quarter

Fantastic work culture within an expanding business

All the tools and resources required to ensure you succeed.

Employer questions:

Your application will include a cover letter with the following:

Why would you like to work for our company?

What interests you about this specific role?

Can you outline your background, experience or qualifications in relevant fields?

If located in Sydney, can you work in our Northern Beaches office 1-2 days a week?

Are you willing to travel to attend our quarterly team meetings in the Byron Bay/Ballina region?

Applicants must be a permanent Australian resident or hold a working visa.

Ready to engineer data systems that actually matter? At Tassal, we’re transforming the way Australia’s largest aquaculture business uses data and we are searching for a mid-level Data Engineer who wants to do work that makes a real impact. As part of Cooke Inc, you will also be connected to a global network of innovators working on the next evolution of analytics, AI and modern data platforms.

Why This Role?

You will step into a pipeline of high value, data driven projects across operations optimisation, advanced analytics, workflow automation and governed data products. You’ll be hands on in shaping the architecture, engineering practices and modern data stack as we move to Snowflake in the near future.

You will work closely with our Senior Data Engineer, helping build the pipelines, tooling and foundations that unlock insights across our business.

If you want to engineer systems that are scalable, battle tested and designed with real world complexity in mind, you will enjoy this role.

What You Will Be Building

You will have scope, ownership and trust to deliver genuine engineering work, including:

• Designing and maintaining high performance data ingestion pipelines from operational systems into our cloud data warehouse
• Developing modern ELT and orchestration workflows using Databricks or Snowflake, Azure Data Factory (ADF), dbt and Fivetran
• Building scalable data models that support analytics, dashboards and mission critical decisions
• Creating application to application integration pipelines to keep Tassal’s digital ecosystem working smoothly
• Championing CI/CD and engineering best practice, including version control, peer reviews, testing and monitoring
• Working with Digital and Data, Business Systems and business stakeholders to translate requirements into reliable architectures and high quality solutions

What You Will Bring

We are looking for someone who is curious, sharp and ready to take on a role with real influence. Ideally, you will have:

• 3 to 5+ years working with Databricks or Snowflake and dbt
• 3 to 5+ years experience in data engineering, analytics engineering or similar
• Experience building efficient, scalable and maintainable data models
• Strong SQL skills with readable and optimised queries
• Experience designing and maintaining automated data pipelines with resiliency and reliable recovery
• A good understanding of data governance, quality frameworks and security best practice
• A commitment to continuous improvement across the Tassal Data Platform

If you enjoy clean code, solid architecture, smart transformations and watching reliable pipelines run smoothly, you will fit in well.

Why Join Tassal?

• Your engineering will influence real world outcomes
• Hybrid work options (WFH after probation)
• A Hobart based role with global opportunities through Cooke Inc
• A supportive and collaborative team that values engineering excellence
• A modern data environment that is evolving quickly, and you get to help shape it

Our Story:

At Tassal Group, we are dedicated to “Sustainably Feeding Tomorrow.” With over 35 years of aquaculture experience, we focus on providing healthy, sustainable, and nutritious food, including salmon, prawn, and barramundi. We are committed to producing accessible food, supporting communities, and delivering strong economic results, all while prioritising sustainability to ensure a prosperous, healthy planet for future generations.

Our Values:

Our people each contribute in different ways, embracing our business values and harnessing our can-do, safety-first culture with purpose and intent. Our shared values are an essential part of our business culture; they define us. They underpin and guide our commitment, attitude, how we work, and the quality of our products. We are passionate, we achieve together, we own it, and we can do it safely.

Please note, you must have full work rights in Australia to be considered for this role.

If you have any questions, please email Joel at joel.sceney@tassal.com.au

St Vincent's has been a leader in Australia's health and aged care landscape for more than 165 years. Since our founders, the Sisters of Charity, opened our first hospital in 1857, our services and nearly 30,000 people have been behind some of Australia's most important medical breakthroughs. We are a microcosm of Australia's health and aged care system and are uniquely positioned to lead and respond to our rapidly changing environment.

Are you an experienced Data Engineering leader ready to shape the future of healthcare technology? Join St Vincent's Health Australia (SVHA) and lead our transformation journey as we build an integrated Data, AI & Interoperability Platform to modernise healthcare delivery. This is your opportunity to pioneer the next generation of healthcare data infrastructure.

The Opportunity

St Vincent's Health Australia (SVHA) is launching its future as a "Connected, Intelligent Healthcare organisation" to unify data, AI and intelligence across our national footprint. As the Data Engineering & Innovation Lead, you will be the platform owner for our modern data and AI platform, guiding St Vincent's through an exciting transformation to cloud & AI-native data capabilities.

This is a unique opportunity to architect and lead the engineering function as we embark on our journey toward real-time IoT data integration, Generative AI and Machine Learning, self-service analytics, and data democratisation across our healthcare ecosystem.

You and your team will be responsible for bring structured and unstructured data from multiple sources at many speeds, transforming it into meaningful inputs for advanced analytics and AI. You will also be leading the establishing and growth of cutting edge AI capabilities as St Vincent's navigates its journey to increasingly embedding AI into the services it provides to its patients and residents.

Working closely with diverse stakeholders across clinical, operational and corporate functions, you'll build strong partnerships and implement process improvements that unlock the power of data to enhance patient care and operational excellence.

This role is part of a broader Data Analytics Community across SVHA, and all activities must align with SVHA's Data Governance & Analytics Strategy and Standards, ensuring we build a sustainable, scalable platform for the future.

What you will be doing.

Key Responsibilities:
As Data Engineering & Innovation Lead, you will be expected to:


Serve as the technical platform owner for our modern Data & AI platform. Lead the design, implementation and evolution of data engineering solutions that enable real-time data processing, IoT integration, and advanced analytics capabilities across the organisation.
Drive innovation through Generative AI and Machine Learning capabilities, establishing frameworks and pipelines that enable predictive analytics, intelligent automation and data-driven decision making to transform patient care and operational efficiency.
Enable data democratisation by building robust, user-friendly data pipelines and self-service analytics capabilities that empower stakeholders across the organisation to access and leverage data insights independently and securely.
Design and implement cloud-native data architectures including data lakes, lakehouses, streaming platforms and interoperability layers. Establish data modelling standards, ETL/ELT processes and data quality frameworks that support scalable, reliable data operations.
Build strong relationships with clinical, operational and technical stakeholders to understand data needs, gather requirements and implement process change management. Act as a trusted advisor on data engineering best practices and innovation opportunities.
Ensure the Mission, Vision, Creed, and Values of SVHA (Compassion, Justice, Integrity, Excellence) are effectively integrated into all areas of responsibility, maintaining ethical data practices and patient-centered technology solutions.

What You'll Bring.

Essential Experience & Skills:

Tertiary qualification Degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field
Extensive experience in data engineering, data architecture, and modern cloud-native data platforms (Azure preferred, Fabric, databricks, snowflake desirable)
Proven track record of leading data engineering initiatives and serving as a platform owner for enterprise data solutions
Strong expertise in data modelling, ETL/ELT pipelines, data warehousing, and real-time data processing
Experience with AI/ML platforms, including Generative AI integration and MLOps practices
Demonstrated ability to design and implement self-service analytics and data democratisation initiatives
Deep understanding of data governance, data quality frameworks, and interoperability standards (particularly in healthcare)
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with ability to translate technical concepts for diverse audiences
Experience driving innovation and continuous improvement in complex organisational environments

Desirable:

Data, infrastructure and/or AI certifications by recognised providers (Microsoft, , Databricks, Snowflake etc.)
Knowledge and experience of the health industry and healthcare data standards (HL7, FHIR)
Experience with IoT data platforms and real-time streaming technologies
Track record of leading digital transformation initiatives in large, complex organisations

If you are driven to achieve results, possess strong technical leadership and innovation skills, and want to contribute to a workplace that is safe and promotes personal wellbeing while transforming healthcare through data and technology, we encourage you to apply.

Things that work for you:

Opportunity to lead the engineering transformation for a major healthcare organisation
Ability to visibly see your impact on patient care and health service delivery
Work with cutting-edge technologies including AI, ML, IoT and modern cloud platforms
Competitive salary packaging options
Discounted private health insurance
Employee Assistance Program for staff and their families
Access to the Fitness Passport (FP)

About HCF

At HCF, our purpose is to bring our human touch to healthcare. Since 1932 we've been putting our members and their health first. As Australia's largest not-for-profit health fund, we cover over 1.9 million members with health, life, travel and pet insurance and our vision is to make healthcare understandable, affordable, high quality and member centric.

We want to be true health partners to our members, easily guiding the healthcare choices that are right for them. At HCF, our values are the way we do things and create the necessary culture to help us realise our purpose and deliver our Strategy. Living our values in action we step forward, walk in their shoes, stay human, make it better and get there together.

Culture & Benefits

Purpose-driven passion
We're united by a common purpose: to make healthcare affordable, understandable, high quality and member-focused.

Wellness and work-life balance
We'll empower you with the necessary skills and tools to support your personal wellbeing journey, ensuring you perform at your best. Our offerings include:
* 50% subsidy on HCF hospital and/or extras cover
* 18 weeks of parental leave for all new parents
* Mental health and wellbeing programs, including workshops, fitness classes, flu vaccinations, skin checks and more
* Discounts on HCF's products, including life, pet and travel Insurance, as well as discounts at Fitness First gyms and on our eyecare products.

Collaboration and inclusivity
We embrace diversity as our strength and are committed to maintaining an inclusive and collaborative work environment. Our workplace is welcoming and safe for all our employees, irrespective of their unique characteristics including age, ethnicity, cultural or spiritual background, gender identity, disability, education and socio-economic status.

Continuous learning and growth
We believe in lifelong learning. HCF provides opportunities for personal and professional development. From workshops to mentorship programs, we encourage your growth and curiosity.



Next steps

If you require any adjustments to assist you in making your application or during the recruitment or onboarding process, please reach out to Talent Acquisition - peopleservices@hcf.com.au to discuss.

We encourage applicants to submit their applications at their earliest convenience, as at HCF, we review applications as they are submitted, and may have filled the role prior to the job closing date.

What you’ll be doing:

Working with data engineers and product teams to turn ideas into working solutions

About Us

At PointsBet, we’ve only built a fraction of what we have imagined. Launched in Australia in 2017, PointsBet has grown into a leader in the online gaming industry, delivering top-tier sportsbook and online gaming experiences to customers across Australia and Canada.

In 2025, PointsBet joined forces with MIXI, Inc., a Tokyo-based digital entertainment company known for pioneering social communication and sports entertainment experiences. Together, we combine MIXI’s deep expertise in building global communities, with PointsBet’s cutting-edge technology and product innovation, unlocking new opportunities to shape the future of digital entertainment.

Driven by a passion for innovation and a strong commitment to responsible gaming, we’re powered by a diverse team that champions safety, integrity and the thrill of the game.

About the Role

As a Data Science Engineer, you will work closely with Trading, Technology, Product, and Analytics Engineering to design, develop, implement, and maintain quantitative models that support our trading operations. Reporting to the Lead Data Scientist, this role combines applied mathematics and statistical modelling with practical engineering skills to ensure models operate effectively in production environments, including real‑time trading systems.

The successful candidate will have a collaborative mindset, an interest in building robust systems rather than one‑off analyses and the desire to see models function reliably in live environments.

Role Responsibilities:

Build and maintain quantitative models to support pricing, risk management, and trading decisions.
Perform exploratory analysis and feature engineering to improve model accuracy and stability.
Develop automation components that support model execution and continuous improvement.
Implement models in production, writing maintainable, production‑grade Python code with appropriate testing and version control.
Deploy models into real‑time and batch trading systems, including containerised environments (e.g., Kubernetes) or platform‑approved runtimes.
Monitor model behaviour in production, including accuracy drift, data issues, and system performance.
Work with Technology and Platform teams to ensure reliable release, rollback, and runtime operation of models.
Collaborate with Analytics Engineering to consume validated, production‑ready datasets and surface any data issues detected during model execution.
Contribute to model validation cycles, incorporate trader feedback, and iterate based on measurable performance.
Adhere to team engineering standards, coding practices, and CI/CD processes to support consistent and reliable model deployment.

Required Skills & Experience:

Strong aptitude in applied mathematics, statistics, or a related quantitative discipline.
Proficiency in Python, with experience writing maintainable, production‑quality code.
Proficiency in SQL and experience working with analytical data platforms (e.g., Databricks).
2+ years in a Data Science Engineer role is preferred.
Hands-on experience building statistical or machine‑learning models in a commercial or applied setting.
Understanding of software engineering fundamentals such as version control, testing, and deployment practices.
Experience integrating models into production systems or containerised environments is advantageous.
Understanding of sports betting, trading systems, or customer behaviour is beneficial.
Logical, analytical approach to problem solving.
Strong organisational and communication skills.

Apply now to start your journey at PointsBet, where your curiosity, grit and ideas can make a real impact.

Don’t meet every requirement on the job description? That’s okay! We encourage you to apply anyway. We are built different at PointsBet, because we think different. We value diverse perspectives and are excited to hear from applicants with unique skill sets. Your individuality and experience could be the perfect addition to our team.

In this hands-on leadership role, you will guide a small team of AI specialists while working closely with software, data, and business stakeholders to ensure AI systems are reliable, scalable, secure, and aligned to organisational goals.

You will lead the delivery of production AI and MLOps solutions in a permanent, hybrid role requiring just one day per week in the office. Working primarily on Azure, you will take a hands-on leadership position, guiding and mentoring a small technical team while ensuring AI systems are robust, scalable, and effectively deployed into production.

St Vincent's has been a leader in Australia's health and aged care landscape for more than 165 years. Since our founders, the Sisters of Charity, opened our first hospital in 1857, our services and nearly 30,000 people have been behind some of Australia's most important medical breakthroughs. We are a microcosm of Australia's health and aged care system and are uniquely positioned to lead and respond to our rapidly changing environment.

Are you an experienced Data Engineering leader ready to shape the future of healthcare technology? Join St Vincent's Health Australia (SVHA) and lead our transformation journey as we build an integrated Data, AI & Interoperability Platform to modernise healthcare delivery. This is your opportunity to pioneer the next generation of healthcare data infrastructure.

The Opportunity

St Vincent's Health Australia (SVHA) is launching its future as a "Connected, Intelligent Healthcare organisation" to unify data, AI and intelligence across our national footprint. As the Data Engineering & Innovation Lead, you will be the platform owner for our modern data and AI platform, guiding St Vincent's through an exciting transformation to cloud & AI-native data capabilities.

This is a unique opportunity to architect and lead the engineering function as we embark on our journey toward real-time IoT data integration, Generative AI and Machine Learning, self-service analytics, and data democratisation across our healthcare ecosystem.

You and your team will be responsible for bring structured and unstructured data from multiple sources at many speeds, transforming it into meaningful inputs for advanced analytics and AI. You will also be leading the establishing and growth of cutting edge AI capabilities as St Vincent's navigates its journey to increasingly embedding AI into the services it provides to its patients and residents.

Working closely with diverse stakeholders across clinical, operational and corporate functions, you'll build strong partnerships and implement process improvements that unlock the power of data to enhance patient care and operational excellence.

This role is part of a broader Data Analytics Community across SVHA, and all activities must align with SVHA's Data Governance & Analytics Strategy and Standards, ensuring we build a sustainable, scalable platform for the future.

What you will be doing.
Key Responsibilities:

As Data Engineering & Innovation Lead, you will be expected to:

Serve as the technical platform owner for our modern Data & AI platform. Lead the design, implementation and evolution of data engineering solutions that enable real-time data processing, IoT integration, and advanced analytics capabilities across the organisation.
Drive innovation through Generative AI and Machine Learning capabilities, establishing frameworks and pipelines that enable predictive analytics, intelligent automation and data-driven decision making to transform patient care and operational efficiency.
Enable data democratisation by building robust, user-friendly data pipelines and self-service analytics capabilities that empower stakeholders across the organisation to access and leverage data insights independently and securely.
Design and implement cloud-native data architectures including data lakes, lakehouses, streaming platforms and interoperability layers. Establish data modelling standards, ETL/ELT processes and data quality frameworks that support scalable, reliable data operations.
Build strong relationships with clinical, operational and technical stakeholders to understand data needs, gather requirements and implement process change management. Act as a trusted advisor on data engineering best practices and innovation opportunities.
Ensure the Mission, Vision, Creed, and Values of SVHA (Compassion, Justice, Integrity, Excellence) are effectively integrated into all areas of responsibility, maintaining ethical data practices and patient-centered technology solutions.

What You'll Bring.

Essential Experience & Skills:

Tertiary qualification Degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field
Extensive experience in data engineering, data architecture, and modern cloud-native data platforms (Azure preferred, Fabric, databricks, snowflake desirable)
Proven track record of leading data engineering initiatives and serving as a platform owner for enterprise data solutions
Strong expertise in data modelling, ETL/ELT pipelines, data warehousing, and real-time data processing
Experience with AI/ML platforms, including Generative AI integration and MLOps practices
Demonstrated ability to design and implement self-service analytics and data democratisation initiatives
Deep understanding of data governance, data quality frameworks, and interoperability standards (particularly in healthcare)
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with ability to translate technical concepts for diverse audiences
Experience driving innovation and continuous improvement in complex organisational environments

Desirable:

Data, infrastructure and/or AI certifications by recognised providers (Microsoft, , Databricks, Snowflake etc.)
Knowledge and experience of the health industry and healthcare data standards (HL7, FHIR)
Experience with IoT data platforms and real-time streaming technologies
Track record of leading digital transformation initiatives in large, complex organisations

If you are driven to achieve results, possess strong technical leadership and innovation skills, and want to contribute to a workplace that is safe and promotes personal wellbeing while transforming healthcare through data and technology, we encourage you to apply.


Things that work for you:

Opportunity to lead the engineering transformation for a major healthcare organisation
Ability to visibly see your impact on patient care and health service delivery
Work with cutting-edge technologies including AI, ML, IoT and modern cloud platforms
Competitive salary packaging options
Discounted private health insurance
Employee Assistance Program for staff and their families
Access to the Fitness Passport (FP)

Our client, providing operational and infrastructure assessment, capacity modelling and optimisation services that support the performance of Queensland’s resources sector, is seeking a Capacity Modeller to join their small, high-performing team of specialists.
  
In this role, you’ll work at the intersection of data, technology, and real-world rail and supply chain operations - delivering simulation insights that directly influence decisions. You will be exposed to complex, multi-stakeholder challenges, cutting‑edge modelling environments, and a culture that values curiosity, innovation, and continuous improvement.

WHAT YOU’LL DO:
As a key member of the Capacity Modelling team, you will:

Collate and input stakeholder data into discrete event simulation modelling tools to assess supply chain and rail network capacity.
Critically analyse, challenge, and interpret model outcomes – identifying key drivers, constraints, and improvement opportunities.
Translate modelling results into clear operational insights, recommendations, and scenarios for decision makers.
Identify data and modelling issues, proposing practical solutions and enhancements.
Work closely with the CEO, Modelling & Reporting Teams and external customers to deliver high-quality, actionable modelling outputs.
Contribute to process improvements and the evolution of modelling frameworks and digital capabilities.
ABOUT YOU:
You thrive in analytical environments and enjoy solving complex problems with real operational and commercial impact. You bring:

Experience in capacity simulation modelling within supply chain, transport, mining, manufacturing, or consulting environments.
Proficiency in discrete event simulation tools such as Anylogic, ExtendSim, Arena or similar.
Qualifications in Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, IT, Supply Chain/Logistics or a related discipline.
Strong data literacy, problem solving capability and intellectual curiosity.
Excellent communication and storytelling skills – able to simplify technical insights for diverse stakeholders.
An interest in digital innovation, modern data platforms, and improving modelling processes.
ON OFFER:
You’ll be part of a small, trusted and collaborative team where your work directly influences the performance of one of the world’s most complex coal supply chains.

A competitive salary package including a performance-related bonus.
Flexible hybrid work arrangements.
The opportunity to work alongside deeply experienced industry experts.
Exposure to cutting-edge tools, including Microsoft Fabric, advanced simulation environments, and modern data automation.
Involvement in complex, multi-stakeholder projects with the ability to drive improvements and change.
A culture that embraces innovation, continuous improvement, and new ideas.
A unique opportunity to develop your skills in a niche, high-impact area of supply chain optimisation.

Work at the forefront of the AI revolution.  Join AFL and be part of our data centre growth journey!  




About AFL    

At AFL, we’re enabling the AI era and shaping the future of connectivity. We connect customers worldwide with innovative technologies, quality products, and exceptional service. Serving Enterprise, Industrial, Service Provider, and Hyperscale markets, we deliver end-to-end fibre connectivity solutions backed by world-class expertise.    

We’re a customer-first, community-centred organisation... and we’re growing fast.  




The Opportunity  

Australia & New Zealand’s data centre industry is booming, and AFL is expanding to meet this demand. It’s an exciting time to join us as we scale and innovate!  

We’re seeking Expressions of Interest across multiple disciplines to help our customers deploy at speed and shape critical infrastructure for the digital future.  

Our dedicated Data Centre Services team are expanding and seeking expressions of interest from dynamic, customer-focussed individuals to help support critical and high-value data centre deployments and structured cabling projects.  

In this impactful role, you will:  

Partner with customers to translate their needs into integrated AFL solutions, including developing reference architectures, network schematics and BOMs, and advising on performance, density, scalability and deployment best practice; 

Provide technical support across the project lifecycle including pre‑sales consulting, solution integration, training and ongoing technical oversight to ensure successful delivery; 

Provide remote or hands on on‑site expertise, including splicing, inspection, testing and commissioning, while troubleshooting and optimising installations to maintain high‑quality outcomes; and 

Elevate our solutions through continuous improvement, capturing Voice‑of‑Customer insights and site learnings to refine AFL’s products, deployment standards and customer experience. 

Note this role is based at our brand new premises in Kilsyth, with hybrid and flexible working options available.


What You’ll Bring  

Relevant experience in data centre operations, structured cabling, or telecommunications, ideally with a relevant engineering qualification.  

Highly analytical and proficient in technical concepts and products 

Customer centric with clear and confident internal and external communication skills, and a passion for solving customer problems under pressure  

Agile, collaborative, and comfortable working at pace with accountability 

A willingness to travel interstate as required
  

If this opportunity excites you but you don’t meet every requirement, we’d still love to hear from you.   




Why AFL    

Join a global leader in fibre optics and make an impact on essential infrastructure. At AFL, you’ll enjoy:    

Working at the cutting edge of technology, with a supportive team and culture  

Highly competitive remuneration   

Genuine career pathways, global exposure and extensive learning & development    

Benefits including hybrid and flexible work options, birthday leave, novated leasing, top-up parental leave, EAP, community outreach, onsite parking, and more  




Ready to grow with us?    

Don’t miss the chance to be part of our growth story. Express your interest today and help shape the future of data centre connectivity!

Ad Text:
Employment type – full time continuing role as a Senior Data Engineer, working within UNSW IT
Starting salary $148012 plus generous superannuation and leave loading
Location: UNSW Kensington Campus (Hybrid Working Opportunities, 2 days in the office)

About UNSW:
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community, a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

UNSW IT is part of UNSW’s Division of Operations and provides high quality, sustainable, flexible products and state of the art services to UNSW. Our priorities are to drive innovative architectures that enable UNSW’s digital future and be a trusted partner of the University. This role is responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining data solutions on UNSW’s data platform. The Senior Data Engineer is responsible for building, implementing, and supporting data solutions and integration components using data technology components. This role combines expertise in data engineering, data modeling, Master Data Management (MDM), and DevOps practices to ensure efficient data pipelines, reliable deployments, and optimal performance of data systems. The position reports to the Lead Solution Architect - MDM and Data and has no direct reports.

Specific accountabilities for this role include:

Lead the development, configuration and implementation of MDM, canonical data models, data persistence layers, data ingestion components, and components integrated into business applications.
Lead the continuous improvement and scale of MDM, central data models, data persistence layers, data ingestion components, and components integrated into business applications.
Provide expert technical and engineering support of MDM, central data models, data persistence layers, data ingestion components, and components integrated into business applications.
Enhance the UNSW IT standard integration platform based on the Microsoft technology stack through collaboration with wider colleagues (including but not limited to Architects, Engineers) and aligned with industry trends and best practise.
Analyse specific requirements and architectures to design appropriate objects and methods for implementing functional and non-functional requirements.
Guide developers, vendor SI and coordinate with internal organisational units and suppliers during implementation to ensure deliverables are met.
Organise infrastructure or data/integration platform changes to integrate applications into the technology landscape.
Design and implement relational database schemas, build data ingestion, transformation, and harmonization pipelines in the Microsoft Azure Platform, and develop SQL queries for data collection from relational databases and data sources.
Proactively manage complex risks, issues, and financials and work with the team to find appropriate solutions.
Support leadership in optimising the Application Integration & Data Services work, including practices, organisation, and resourcing for continuous improvement.
Oversee effective communications with key stakeholders, internal and external, and provide influential input to achieve business outcomes.

Who you are:

Tertiary qualifications in IT or a related discipline, with 7+ years of experience in software development using Cloud architectures and middleware components.
Extensive experience in enterprise master data management platforms, data engineering technologies, data modelling, integration, and data design practice, including SQL queries and database schemas.
Hands-on experience with Informatica Cloud MDM / Customer 360 / Product 360 with expertise in match & merge rules, survivorship logic, hierarchies, workflows, and Golden Record creation. Informatica experience would be essential as this is our key platform.
Proficiency in designing and implementing solutions using Azure data services (MS SQL, Synapse, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Bricks, Azure Data Lake, Azure Storage Accounts, Azure Service Bus).
Experience with a diverse array of synchronous and asynchronous integration patterns (e.g., API, ESB, ETL) in appropriate settings.
Strong skills in ETL/ELT tools (Informatica PowerCenter, IDMC, Azure Data Factory)
Extensive experience with the development of data solutions to support API integrations. • Strong understanding of application, data, and API security and privacy controls.
Experience with Azure DevOps and CI/CD tools for automated testing and deployment of data related solutions and database schema changes.
Knowledge of system integration methods, products, tools, development life cycle, and their impact on integrated solutions.
Knowledge of technical products like Terraform, Ansible, Docker, Kubernetes, Databricks, Artifactory, and productivity applications like Git, Jira, and Confluence is preferred.
Advanced written and verbal communication skills with attention to detail.
Excellent time management skills, ability to respond to changing priorities, manage multiple tasks, and meet deadlines.
Familiarity with Agile Project Management methodologies and experience in participating in storyboarding, estimation, and using project management tools.
An understanding of and commitment to UNSW’s aims, objectives and values in action, together with relevant policies and guidelines.
Knowledge of health and safety responsibilities and commitment to attending relevant health and safety training.

Benefits and Culture

Flexible Working Options (work from home, flexible hours etc) 
Career development opportunities
17% Superannuation contributions and additional leave loading payments 
Additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period
Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness)

For further details on the benefits, please visit https://www.jobs.unsw.edu.au/lifestyle-benefits

How to Apply: please apply through the portal, we would like you to submit a full application including resume and addressing the who you are section.

Applications close:  Feb 10th at 11.30pm

Pre-Employment Checks
Aligned with UNSW’s focus on cultivating a workplace defined by safety, ethical conduct, and strong integrity preferred candidates will be required to participate in a combination of pre-employment checks relevant to the role they have applied for.

These pre-employment checks may include a combination of some of the following checks:- 

National and International Criminal history checks
Entitlement to work and ID checks
Working With Children Checks
Completion of a Gender-Based Violence Prevention Declaration
Verification of relevant qualifications
Verification of relevant professional membership
Employment history and reference checks
Financial responsibility assessments/checks.
Medical Checks and Assessments

Compliance with the necessary combination of these checks is a condition of employment at UNSW.

The Company
A global industrial technology organisation supplying advanced food processing, automation and digital solutions to manufacturers across meat, poultry, seafood and prepared foods, with a strong focus on efficiency, food safety and long-term operational performance.

This is a hands-on, autonomous role for a technically capable Field Service Engineer who enjoys working directly with customers and advanced equipment in a fast-moving environment.

The Role
As a Field Service Engineer, you will provide technical support for both installed systems and new equipment installations at customer sites. This role combines preventative maintenance, fault finding, system optimisation and customer engagement.

You’ll work closely with customers to ensure equipment performance, reliability and service expectations are consistently met.

Key Responsibilities


Carry out preventative maintenance visits, including preparation, execution and reporting


Attend customer sites to diagnose and resolve production and equipment issues


Perform breakdown and repair services on high-technology food processing equipment


Install machine upgrades and enhancements, testing and calibrating equipment to specification


Troubleshoot complex electrical and control system faults


Support new installations and commissioning activities


Maintain clear, professional communication with customer management and site teams


What We’re Looking For


Industrial electrical trade background or equivalent experience


PLC knowledge with the ability to diagnose and repair complex control systems


Ability to read and interpret electrical schematics and circuit diagrams


3–5 years’ experience in a manufacturing environment (FMCG highly regarded)


Familiarity with conveyors, process lines, motors, VSDs and automation equipment


Flexibility to work weekends or out-of-hours when required


If you’re looking for a technically challenging role where no two days are the same and where your expertise genuinely adds value for customers, this is an opportunity worth exploring.

Company Description


This is your opportunity to join our team of forward-thinking, change-making individuals. Operating at the intersection of health and tech, you'll help us shape the future of healthcare. 

Our Mission

Healthengine’s mission is to improve access to healthcare by helping Australians find and connect with all care providers. We strive to achieve this through Australia’s leading healthcare marketplace, bringing together over 4 million active Australians, and more than 10 thousand practitioners that are powered by our technology - and growing.

We’re all patients, right? So, it’s easy to get behind a mission that seeks to improve the healthcare experience for all Australians. 

Job Description


The Gig

This role sits at the intersection of enablement, innovation, and scaling—supercharging every engineer with advanced AI tools and workflows while exploring and prototyping the latest in AI developer technology. You'll also help standardise secure, high-performing AI environments across the business.

If your background is primarily in data analysis, reporting, or BI, this role is unlikely to be a good fit.

Responsibilities:

Continuously explore, evaluate, and test emerging AI technologies to identify opportunities that could enhance engineering productivity and developer experience
Monitor the performance, adoption, and effectiveness of existing engineering tools to understand usage patterns, gaps, and opportunities for improvement
Build quick, effective prototypes, such as prompts or workflows that enable engineers to auto-generate Jira tasks, trigger background agents, and create PR-ready code with minimal input.
Provide guidance and hands-on support to engineers looking to elevate their AI tooling skills
Track and optimise AI tooling and infrastructure costs to ensure efficient, scalable, and sustainable usage across the engineering organisation.
Care and commitment to information security practices to protect Healthengine and its customers

About You

You're the kind of person who takes accountability in a fast-paced, autonomous and flexible environment. Fast may be your default (like us!) but you never, ever compromise on what’s important, willing to take a steady, more informed approach when it comes to maintaining the trust of our team and customers. You handle change like a pro, and continuous improvement is a way of life. You are not afraid to speak up and share your thoughts respectfully, with the intention of making positive change. You take initiative and drive your own learning journey without waiting for someone to point you in the right direction. And ultimately, you care: about people, health and innovation. 

Experience you’ll bring:

Demonstrated track record of delivery of major technical initiatives, particularly those focused on developer tooling or internal platforms.
Typically 4+ years successful execution at the Senior Engineer role or higher.
Proven experience designing, building, and deploying AI-powered developer tools or workflows (e.g., code generation, task automation, prompt engineering).
Hands-on experience with LLMs/Generative AI technologies and platforms (e.g., prompt development, fine-tuning, RAG architectures, model integration).
Experience with engineering productivity metrics, monitoring, and optimization of internal tooling adoption and effectiveness.
Experience using and implementing CI/CD systems, with an emphasis on automation within the SDLC.
Demonstrated experience mentoring, training, and providing hands-on support to engineers on new tools and best practices.

Company Description


This is your opportunity to join our team of forward-thinking, change-making individuals. Operating at the intersection of health and tech, you'll help us shape the future of healthcare. 

Our Mission

Healthengine’s mission is to improve access to healthcare by helping Australians find and connect with all care providers. Job Description


The Gig

This role sits at the intersection of enablement, innovation, and scaling—supercharging every engineer with advanced AI tools and workflows while exploring and prototyping the latest in AI developer technology. You'll also help standardise secure, high-performing AI environments across the business.

If your background is primarily in data analysis, reporting, or BI, this role is unlikely to be a good fit.

Responsibilities:

Continuously explore, evaluate, and test emerging AI technologies to identify opportunities that could enhance engineering productivity and developer experience

Provide guidance and hands-on support to engineers looking to elevate their AI tooling skills
Track and optimise AI tooling and infrastructure costs to ensure efficient, scalable, and sustainable usage across the engineering organisation.
Care and commitment to information security practices to protect Healthengine and its customers

About You

You're the kind of person who takes accountability in a fast-paced, autonomous and flexible environment. Fast may be your default (like us!) but you never, ever compromise on what’s important, willing to take a steady, more informed approach when it comes to maintaining the trust of our team and customers. You handle change like a pro, and continuous improvement is a way of life. You are not afraid to speak up and share your thoughts respectfully, with the intention of making positive change. You take initiative and drive your own learning journey without waiting for someone to point you in the right direction. And ultimately, you care: about people, health and innovation. 

Experience you’ll bring:

Demonstrated track record of delivery of major technical initiatives, particularly those focused on developer tooling or internal platforms.
Typically 4+ years successful execution at the Senior Engineer role or higher.
Proven experience designing, building, and deploying AI-powered developer tools or workflows (e.g., code generation, task automation, prompt engineering).
Hands-on experience with LLMs/Generative AI technologies and platforms (e.g., prompt development, fine-tuning, RAG architectures, model integration).
Experience with engineering productivity metrics, monitoring, and optimization of internal tooling adoption and effectiveness.
Experience using and implementing CI/CD systems, with an emphasis on automation within the SDLC.
Demonstrated experience mentoring, training, and providing hands-on support to engineers on new tools and best practices.

We are seeking a talent on AI/ML to join our Bigdata team. This role offers hands-on experience in developing advanced algorithms for Know Your Customer (KYC) and Know Your Business (KYB) products.

You’ll work on innovative projects involving computer vision, deep learning, and large language models (LLMs) to tackle real-world challenges in identity verification and fraud detection.

This talent is ideal for Master/PhD students passionate about AI and eager to contribute to high-impact fintech solutions.

Key Responsibilities

Collaborate with the team to design, implement, and optimize algorithms for KYC/KYB processes, including Optical Character Recognition (OCR), face recognition, image quality assurance, and document tampering detection.
Apply traditional deep learning techniques to improve model accuracy and efficiency in image processing and analysis.
Leverage Large Language Models (LLMs) to enhance algorithm capabilities, such as integrating multimodal AI for better document understanding and anomaly detection.
Conduct experiments, analyze data, and iterate on models to ensure robustness and scalability in production environments.
Assist in research and development of new features to strengthen Binance’s compliance and security frameworks.
Participate in code reviews, team meetings, and knowledge-sharing sessions to foster a collaborative environment.
Qualifications and Requirements

Currently enrolled in a PhD program (or equivalent advanced degree) in Computer Science (CS), Electrical Engineering (EE), Information Systems (IS), or a related field at a top university.
Strong background in machine learning, deep learning, and AI frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow).
A big plus: Experience or coursework in computer vision, including techniques for image processing, object detection, or facial recognition.
Familiarity with LLMs and their applications in multimodal tasks is highly desirable.
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, with experience in data processing libraries (e.g., OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas).
Excellent problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and the ability to work independently or in a team.
Passion for blockchain, fintech, or AI ethics is a bonus.
